Nigeria’s GTBank Targets 15% Loan Growth in 2011, ThisDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-05-16T09:02:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/nigeria-s-gtbank-targets-15-loan-growth-in-2011-thisday-says.html
Guaranty Trust Bank Plc (GUARANTY) , a Nigerian
lender, plans to expand its loan book by 15 percent this year,
 ThisDay  reported, citing the bank’s acting managing director,
Segun Agbaje.  The lender achieved 5 percent loan growth in 2010 after
setting a 10 percent target, the Lagos-based newspaper said.
Total loans in 2010 were 594 billion naira ($3.8 billion).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 